Totally surprised to see that the next version of the Linux kernel [http://permalink.gmane.org/gmane.linux.kernel/1147415 will be 3.0]. For a long time, Linus has said there was never going to be any reason to bump the major version number; it was all about steady incremental improvements. Well, finally there is a reason: the small incremental improvements are still with us, but Linus was getting uncomfortable counting up to 40...
